{'taskname': 'clothov21', 'filepath1': 'ClothoV21/development/Steps Indoor medium soft Shoe Sole accompanying wooden Floor hollow Big Room 6mx15mx6m Part 1.wav', 'filepath2': '', 'caption1': "['A basketball is being bounced on the ground at an even pace.', 'Someone climbs the stairs, stomping them as they climbs.', 'An basketball is being bounced on the ground at an even pace.', 'Someone bouncing a basketball on a carpet floor.', 'Someone is bouncing a basketball on a carpeted floor.']", 'caption2': '', 'input': 'Based on the audio, what can be said about the hypothesis - "A basketball is being bounced rhythmically on a floor."? a) It is definitely true b) It is definitely false c) It is plausible d) I cannot determine', 'answer': 'a) It is definitely true', 'subtype': 'CLE.json'}
{'taskname': 'clothov21', 'filepath1': 'ClothoV21/development/Int- Mom&amp;DadcondoScreenDoor.wav', 'filepath2': 'ClothoV21/development/Living Minute - Noisy Neighborhood at Night.wav', 'caption1': 'A squeaking screen door opens and closes two times.', 'caption2': 'Two dogs are barking while the alarm of a ambulance travels a short distance.', 'input': 'explain the difference in detail', 'answer': 'As I listen to the two audios, I notice that the first audio, featuring a squeaking screen door, is characterized by a sharp, high-pitched sound with a sudden onset and decay, lasting only a brief duration. The sound is repetitive, with the door opening and closing twice, creating a sense of rhythmic structure. In contrast, the second audio, featuring two dogs barking and an ambulance alarm, is more complex and dynamic. The barking dogs produce a range of frequencies, from low rumbles to high-pitched yips, with varying loudness and duration. The ambulance alarm adds a piercing, high-pitched tone that cuts through the barking, creating a sense of urgency and chaos. The overall texture of the second audio is more chaotic and unpredictable, with multiple sound sources interacting in a way that creates a sense of tension and drama.', 'subtype': 'CLD-3.json'}
